land]] || Decision || 3 || 3:00 \n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-07-12 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|IRN}} [[Big Ben Chor Praram 6]]  || Thepprasit Stadium || [[Pattaya]], [[Thailand]] || Decision || 5 || 3:00 \n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-05-22 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|IRN}} Behzad Rafigh Doust || WMA Tournament, Finals || [[Zhengzhou]], [[China]] || Decision || 3 || 3:00 \n|- \n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small|Wins the WMA 71kg title.}}\n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-05-22 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|SVK}} Egon Racz || WMA Tournament, Semi-finals || [[Zhengzhou]], [[China]] || Decision || 3 || 3:00 \n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-05-22 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|CAN}} Alain Sylvestre || WMA Tournament, Quarter-finals || [[Zhengzhou]], [[China]] || KO || 1 ||  \n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-01-31 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|THA}} Thepsutin Pumpanmuang || Channel 7 Boxing Stadium || [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] || TKO (Injury) || 5 ||\n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-01-07 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|GBR}} Stephen Meikle || The Champions Club Thailand, Finals || [[Pattaya]], [[Thailand]] || KO || 1 ||    \n|- \n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small|Wins the TCC super welterweight title.}}\n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2010-01-07 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|GBR}} Jason Woodham || The Champions Club Thailand, Semi-finals || [[Pattaya]], [[Thailand]] || TKO || 1 ||    \n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2009-12-22 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|THA}} Pornpitak Petchudomchai || Chaweng Boxing Stadium || [[Ko Samui]], [[Thailand]] || TKO || 2 || \n\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 2009-12-22 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|THA}} Pornpitak Petchudomchai || Chaweng Boxing Stadium || [[Ko Samui]